ias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/10\/18\/tongue-moist-dhikr-allah\/","url_meta":{"origin":25280,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Dhikr: Keep your tongue always remembering Allah","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 18, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Busr reported: A\u00a0man said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, the laws of Islam are too many for me, so tell me something\u00a0I\u00a0can hold onto.\u201d The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cKeep your tongue moist with the remembrance of Allah.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 3375 Grade:\u00a0Sahih\u00a0(authentic)\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":34824,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/12\/27\/adhan-la-hawla-wa-la-quwwah\/","url_meta":{"origin":25280,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Adhan: Responding to come to prayer, come to salvation","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 27, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Yahya ibn Abi Kathir reported: Some of our brethren narrated to me that when the caller to prayer says, \u201cCome to the prayer,\u201d one says, \u201cThere is no movement or might but in Allah.\u201d Mu\u2019awiyah said, \u201cI heard it said likewise by your Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him.\u201d\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25903,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/02\/05\/dua-night-answered\/","url_meta":{"origin":25280,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Dua: Supplication for good at night is answered","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 5, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Mu\u2019adh ibn Jabal reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cNo Muslim retires for the night in a state of remembrance and purification, then wakes up in the night and asks Allah for goodness in the world and the Hereafter, except that he will be given it.\u201d\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":38829,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2023\/02\/18\/dhikr-mawt-hope\/","url_meta":{"origin":25280,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Death: Remembering death balances hope in the Hereafter","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 18, 2023","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Umar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cRemember often the destroyer of pleasures: death. Verily, no one living with plenty does so but that it diminishes his vain hopes, nor one living with little but that it increases his hope in Allah.\u201d Source:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":34795,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/12\/24\/dhikr-for-strength\/","url_meta":{"origin":25280,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Dhikr: Remember Allah for strength to keep working","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 24, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Ali reported: Fatimah complained about blisters on her hands from working the millstone and she asked for a servant. The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cShall I not tell you what is better than you ask for? When both of you lay down to sleep, exalt Allah\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":31840,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/08\/ibn-masud-friends-dhikr\/","url_meta":{"origin":25280,"position":5},"title":"Ibn Mas\u2019ud on Friends: Choose companions who remind you of Allah","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 8, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu al-Ahwas reported: Abdullah ibn Mas\u2019ud, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cRemember Allah Almighty often. You must not accompany anyone unless they help you remember Allah Almighty.\u201d Source: Shu\u2019ab al-Ima\u0304n 8998 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0623\u064e\u062d\u0652\u0648\u064e\u0635\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0646 \u0645\u0633\u0639\u0648\u062f \u0631\u0636\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0639\u0646\u0647 \u0623\u064e\u0643\u0652\u062b\u0650\u0631\u064f\u0648\u0627 \u0630\u0650\u0643\u0652\u0631\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0632\u0651\u064e \u0648\u064e\u062c\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e \u0648\u064e\u0644\u0627\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"hei